title: Ask HN: How to go from data science to software engineering?
text:
I’m a data scientist working in Tech, and have decent programming skills for a data science position, but don’t have a software engineering background. I’ve found that I don’t quite enjoy the ad hoc nature of the profession, moving from one small project to another completely different one. I’d rather work on a project that builds something and the effort accumulates into something more tangible than an analysis report.
What’s the optimal way to learn the necessary software engineering skills and move to such a role?

Ask HN: Is Musk’s emphasis on simplicity going to change the software industry?
text: Assuming that Elon Musk knows, or quickly figures out what he’s doing, and decides to simplify Twitter’s architecture and reduce the accidental complexity that seems to have crept into software development in recent years, what impact will that have on software development as a field?
